Upon logging into ActiveCampaign after a while, I encountered a message that says: &amp;quot;An error occured with your domain authentication. The domain does not have correct CNAME and/or DMARC records. Please double check all records have been created and check DNS again.&amp;quot; 
We use Bluehost for hosting. Bluehost support says: &amp;quot;Based on the error, this will occur if you are adding a record to a zone that already contains similar types (A records, CNAME records, TXT records, or MX records, for example) with already defined TTL values. If you are adding a zone with a different TTL value, the error will appear. 
 Please ensure that all records of the same type share the same TTL values. For example, if a TXT record exists with a TTL of 14400, all TXT records in the zone must share that TTL value. For domains that are pointed here (using our Nameservers), you can add, edit, or delete your DNS entries in the Zone Editor, and if you&#039;re not sure which record is which or which does what, check out DNS Record Definitions for more information.&amp;quot;
Please walk me through the fix on a screenshare to get ActiveCampaign delivering again.<b>Skills</b>:        DNS,                     Email Deliverability,                     ActiveCampaign

